A magistrate court sitting in Osogbo, Osun State has sentenced a 30-year-old woman, Jimoh Sadiat to 6months imprisonment for stealing goat. Sadiat was arraigned on Tuesday and pleaded guilty to two count charge bordering on conspiracy and stealing. Saidat told the court that she wanted to use the proceeds from the goat for her son’s treatment. The prosecutor, Abiodun Fagboyinbo told court that, “Jimoh Sadiat  and one other at large on the 5th of January, 2020 at Agunbelewo area Osogbo in the Osogbo did conspire together to commit felony to wit stealing. “Saidat did steal she don’t value N45,000 property of one Fausat Adegboga.” Fagboyinbo said, “the offence committed is contrary to and punishable under section 516 and 390(9) of the Criminal Code Cap 34 Vol. Laws of Osun State Nigeria 2002.” The defense counsel, Abimbola Ige prayed the court to tender justice with mercy to his client. The Magistrate sentenced Saidat to sentenced  6months imprisonment with N 15,000  option of fine.